FULL NEMETIC STRING:
Φ(MetacognitiveAgency) = σ(memetic_analysis|dialectical_synthesis) ∘ ρ(cognitive_dependency|self-awareness) ∘ λ(paradigm_disruption|third_path_emergence) ∘ β(memetic_evolution|metaphor_cultivation) ∘ δγ(design_ethics|interface_substrate) ∘ μ(interruptibility|structural_choice_architecture) + ε | :reflexive_autonomy

OPERATOR BREAKDOWN:

σ — Air / Aerunik (emphasis: 0.74)
  The analytical dimension maps two competing memeplexes circulating through cultural
  discourse. Memeplex A: AI as cognitive exoskeleton — extending human capability,
  offloading routine tasks, amplifying intelligence. Memeplex B: AI as cognitive
  crutch — eroding human skill, creating dependency, atrophying capacities through
  disuse. Air reveals both as structurally complete but empirically partial: each
  captures genuine dynamics while excluding the other's valid observations. The
  dialectical synthesis is not a compromise but a reframing that makes both memes
  legible as aspects of a more complex phenomenon.

ρ — Water / Sentaria (emphasis: 0.66)
  The felt dimension of cognitive dependency — the subtle experience of reaching for
  AI assistance before attempting one's own thought, the anxiety of composing without
  autocomplete, the relief of delegating difficult reasoning. Self-awareness of these
  felt states constitutes the emotional core of metacognitive agency. Water here is
  not deep but diagnostic: the capacity to notice one's own cognitive-emotional
  relationship to AI tools is the prerequisite for choosing that relationship
  consciously.

λ — Fire / Jvalion (emphasis: 0.78)
  The dominant operator. The third path — metacognitive agency — represents a genuine
  paradigm disruption, not merely a middle position between augmentation and atrophy.
  It reframes the question from "what does AI do to us?" to "how do we choose to
  engage with AI?" This shift from passive object to active agent transforms the
  entire problem space. Fire captures the disruptive, catalytic quality of this
  reframing — it does not moderate the debate but escapes it.

β — Wood / Arboriel (emphasis: 0.69)
  Cultural narratives about AI are not static but evolving memetic organisms. The
  augmentation and atrophy memes will continue to grow, mutate, and recombine. Wood
  captures the developmental trajectory: from initial polarity through memetic fusion
  toward increasingly nuanced metaphors for human-AI relationship. The source text
  explicitly calls for cultivating better metaphors as a cultural practice.

δγ — Earth / Humavita (emphasis: 0.72)
  Metacognitive agency does not emerge in a vacuum but requires specific material
  conditions. Interface design, default settings, friction points, notification
  architectures — these constitute the earth-substrate that either supports or
  undermines reflective engagement. Design ethics that foreground interruptibility
  (the ability to pause and reflect mid-interaction) are material preconditions
  for the agency this encoding describes.

μ — Metal / Ferrosid (emphasis: 0.70)
  Structural mechanisms that scaffold reflection: mandatory pause points, usage
  dashboards, cognitive load indicators, alternative-path prompts. Metal provides
  the architectural rigor that prevents metacognitive agency from remaining a purely
  aspirational concept. Without built-in interruptibility, even the most self-aware
  user will default to habitual patterns under cognitive load.

Z-STATE: :reflexive_autonomy
  The agent maintains conscious awareness of their own cognitive relationship to AI
  tools and actively chooses engagement modes rather than defaulting to habit or
  cultural meme. This is not anti-AI or pro-AI but meta-AI: a stance toward one's
  own stance.

TENDENCY: λ → 0.78
  Fire leads. This is fundamentally a paradigm-disruption encoding — the central
  contribution is the third path that escapes the augmentation/atrophy binary.
  All other operators serve this disruptive reframing.

